<br />
<br />
    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">ADVENTURE DECK STRATEGY<br />
<br />
Use the Green Dragon Inn to pull Sam, you will usually always go first because you can bid up to about 6 burdens.  Once you get out Sam, exert him to get rid of those burdens.  Breeland Forest gets a jump on Hobbit decks that rely on Stealth events to make it through the first 5 sites.  Council Courtyard allows you to remove two Twilight before you leave Elrond&#39;s house.  The Moria Lake gives the most Twilight, and causes an exertion or two.  The Bridge is just the Bridge.  Lothlorien Woods is a Forest for using ARV.  Anduin Wilderland skips the Archery phase, this works well with all of the other SoS&#39;s.  The Shores of Nen Hithoel is a River for ARV, and the Slopes let you pull off a site 9 swarm, in case your opponent survives to the last site.<br />
<br />
FREE PEOPLES STRATEGY<br />
<br />
This deck basically adds the power of Gandalf to the Ranger Archery backbone that we all know and love.  With Sleep, Caradhras, annoying little Sauron decks will fail against you.  Servant of the Secret Fire will keep your opponents heavy hitting minions in the flyweight division.  ARV and Archery is the main drive of the deck, and Strength of Spirit reduces the pain of having to exert to wound ( or kill )  but if anyone gets by to Skirmish, you will have Gwemegil, Swordsman of the Northern Kingdom and Servant of the Secret Fire to keep you alive.  Armor is to stop Damage +1 or more from hurting too badly.  Power According to His Stature and Sting will help save Frodo from an embarassing wetting of his little Hobbit breeches.<br />
<br />
<br />
SHADOW STRATEGY<br />
<br />
The basic Uruk-Hai strategy is brute power, using Lurtz and a 3 Twilight minion to get Lurtz Fierce.  The Soldiers can be Fierce if your opponent is dumb enough to play 5 companions.  This is also a great time for Savagery to Match Their Numbers.  Spies of Saruman shuts down Archery altogether, so Ranger decks better beware.  This deck will Skirmish you, and it will usually win.  Lurtz has overwhelmed a beefy Aragorn with Bred for Battle, Savagery and Saruman&#39;s Ambition.  Lurtz Battle Cry insures the one turn death of Arwen, Legolas, Gimli, Boromir, Haldir, etc.  No real thought on this side, just brute strength.  <br />
 </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
